title: For Trade:  Last call rem 700 Tac
postcontent: Ok guys last call, I've pretty well had my fill of the games.  Remington 700 Tactical, this is not the cheaper and longer barreled AAC-SD or other suffixed models. This model has the 16.5 inch heavy threaded barrel and Hogue rubber over molded stock in Gillie Green. Not only does this feature give a solid positive grip in any hand placement for the shooter but it also acts as a sound deadner for tactical and hunting applications. It is currently topped with a NC Star 2.5-12×40 scope featuring a 30mm body, target style turrets, and dual illuminated mil dot reticle. The scope is mounted with a one piece Leopold scope base and 30mm Leopold rings. I also have the 6 lug rings that came with the scope for mounting to a picitiny rail if you choose to mount this scope on a different rifle or choose a different picitiny base on this rifle. I also have 187 rounds of mixed ammo for the rifle. All ammo is factory loaded, no hand loads, and this rifle has never fired a hand load. It blows my mind what some guys are calling a "sniper rifle" on here these days. This is a true factory purpose built sniper rifle. It is very accurate out to 300 yards. It' very likely it will do just as well at longer ranges, I just haven't had the opportunity to shoot it any farther.  With everything listed I just sat down and added up what I have spent on the whole package. I'm consertively $1250 into it. I say consertively because I'm not pulling the normal BS of adding in taxes, shipping, and rounded down to the nearest 10 from what I actually paid. Not the highest price I could find on the internet or judging from high priced auction sites like gunbroker. I really prefer to just cut out the middle men and trade directly to what I list below. But because of all the "how much cash" emails I've received, I will entertain serious cash offers.
